Engineering Physics, OSU I have worked for the Center for Cosmology and AstroParticle Physics (CCAPP) since July 2009. CCAPP, a partnership between the Departments of Astronomy and Physics, accelerates collaborative research at the interface of cosmology, astrophysics and high-energy physics, providing young scientists an exceptional environment for discovery. CCAPP also educates the public through public lectures and mini-workshops coupled to CCAPP science initiatives. ccapp.osu.edu
